nagios is system and network monitoring application ( open source tool ).

What is it (Nagios) for:

1. It watches hosts, which includes Local or Personal workstation and Remote hosts, which are sitting and running 1000 miles away from your location ( probably servers in data centers ).

2. Nagios can help you to monitor your business critical application running on the host, and Nagios will alert you when services required for application go down or stopped or un-responsive.

3. Nagios will provide optional web-interface for seeing and understanding services which are CRITICAL and which are OK, and Problem history of each configured service.

System Requirement:

1. Any Unix flavour, C compiler and also probably have tcp/ip configured.

2. Any Web server ( if you decided to use CGI )

